description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a flexible position where you can pick and choose where and when you work? If the answer is yes, joining the Bank at the Countess of Chester Hospital could be just for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By being accepted on to the Nurse Bank, you will be provided with access to our Employee Online Rostering app, which means that you can see which shifts are available at the times you wish to work. You will receive notifications of managers looking for certain skill sets and can select the available shifts that suit you. Interested? Please see details below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who our Opportunity is for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are looking for highly motivated and enthusiastic Registered Nurses to join our Bank and support a busy Nursing Division. You will support with filling gaps on the Band 5 rosta at the Countess of Chester Hospital NHS Foundation Trust, having the opportunity to work at Ellesmere Port Hospital.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applicants must be NMC registered and have recent experience working in a hospital environment preferably within the NHS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good time management skills, organisational skills and an ability to work under pressure are essential requirements to this post.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What this Opportunity means: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A local induction will be provided at the beginning of a worker agreement as well as ongoing mandatory training as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A friendly and supportive working environment (see our &lt;strong&gt;Trust Behavioural Standards&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Salary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePractice Development TeamEmail addresscoc-tr.PracticeDevelopmentTeam@nhs.netTelephone number01244 364009&lt;/p&gt;
